l II of Savoy]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-vac|last=Louis XVI}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Co-Princes of Andorra|Co-Prince of Andorra]]|years=1806 \u2013 11 April 1814|alongside1=[[Francesc Antoni de la Due\u00f1a y Cisneros|Francesc Antoni de la Due\u00f1a]]}}\n{{S-aft|after=Louis XVIII}}\n{{s-new|reason=State created}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Protector of the Confederation of the Rhine]]|years=12 July 1806 \u2013 19 October 1813}}\n{{s-non|reason=Confederation dissolved|reason2=successive ruler:<br />[[Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor|Francis I of Austria]]<br />''as [[President of the German Confederation|Head of the ''Pr\u00e4sidialmacht'' Austria]]''}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-new}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Sovereign of the [[Elba|Island of Elba]]|years=11 April 1814 \u2013 20 March 1815}}\n{{S-non|reason=Relinquished title}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{S-bef|before=Louis XVIII|as=King of France and Navarre}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Emperor of the French<br />Co-Prince of Andorra|years=20 March \u2013 22 June 1815}}\n{{S-aft|after=Louis XVIII|as=King of France and Navarre<br />([[Napoleon II]] '''according to his will only''')}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{S-pre|}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-new}}\n{{s-tul|title=Emperor of the French|years=11 April 1814&nbsp;\u2013 20 March 1815}}\n{{s-vac|next=Napoleon II}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Napoleonic Wars}}\n{{French Revolution navbox}}\n{{Imperial House of France (First French Empire)}}\n{{Bonaparte family}}\n{{German Confederations 1806\u20131871}}\n{{French Pretenders}}\n{{Heads of state of France}}\n{{French Consulate}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Napoleon| ]]\n[[Category:1769 births]]\n[[Category:1821 deaths]]\n[[Category:18th-century heads of state of France]]\n[[Category:19th-century monarchs of France]]\n[[Category:19th-century Princes of Andorra]]\n[[Category:19th-century kings of Italy]]\n[[Category:Protector of the Confederation of the Rhine]]\n[[Category:Amateur mathematicians]]\n[[Category:French art collectors]]\n[[Category:Characters in War and Peace]]\n[[Category:Corsican politicians]]\n